le piredes cas conservant comportement c2ab orienté objectif c2bb méthodedes tableaux standard   recherche solutions effectuée unespace réduit  algorithme implémenté prototype  nomméstaré  évalué diverses ontologies  deuxièmement  me suisintéressé augmenter pouvoir expression logique descriptionen rajoutant fermeture transitive relations binaires estmontrée connecteur logique intéressant modélisation desconnaissances  aide méthode tableaux compressés sert nonseulement optimisation détermination décidabilitéd langage  avons montré qu nouveau langage résultant unecombinaison libre logique description expressive fermeturetransitive indécidable  résultat permis proposer unerestriction laquelle nouveau langage devient décidable  letroisième aspect concerne révision ontologie expressive lorsqu nouvelle connaissance ajoutée ontologie  cettedernière pourrait devenir incohérente  afin restaurer cohérence  ilest nécessaire changer ontologie initiale telle façon lechangement soit minimal nouvelle connaissance soit prise comptedans ontologie résultante  avons proposé méthode révision quirepose caractérisation sémantique ontologie enutilisant ensemble fini graphes représentation modèlesd ontologie  méthode implémentée prototype mis ligne nommé ontorev mots clés   raisonnement  révision  ontologie  logiques description méthode tableauxabstract   this habilitation thesis outlines methods and tools resultingfrom my research activities during the last nine years  these methods andtools have been developed for reasoning and revision on knowledge basesused in the context of the semantic web where data and knowledge stored inthese bases would be represented in langage equipped with formal andunambiguous semantics  such formal semantics makes possible to develop anautomated mechanism for reasoning on the kind of such knowledge bases whichare called ontologies in this thesis  in order to address the requirementsfor representing and exchanging data in the context of the semantic web description logics  decidable fragment of first order logic  are used for encoding  the semantics of the language owl  ontology web language  thatwas adopted by w3c  was interested in developing algorithms and toolswhich allow for processing data and knowledge represented in descriptionlogics  my research therefore focuses on the three following topics  first it is the development of an optimized tableau method  called compressedtableau  for reasoning on expressive ontologies  this method allows toobtain worst case optimal algorithm in preserving the c2ab goal oriented c2bbbehavior of the standard tableau method   searching performed in areduced space  the method has been implemented in the prototype  namedstaré  and evaluated with various ontologies  second  was interested inaugmenting the expression power of description logics by adding thetransitive closure of binary relations which is known as an interestinglogical connector for knowledge modeling  by using the compressed tableaumethod which allows not only for optimization but also for determiningdecidability of language  we have showed that new language obtained byfully combining an expressive description logic with the transitive closuremay be undecidable  this result led us to propose restriction whichenables the new langage to be decidable  the third topic of my research isconcerned with expressive ontology revision  when adding new knowledge toan ontology  it may become inconsistent  in order to restore consistency ofthe ontology  it is needed to change the initial ontology in such waythat the change should be minimal and the new knowledge should be takeninto account in the resulting ontology  we have proposed revision methodwhich relies on characterization of the semantics of an ontology by usinga finite set of graphs for representing ontology models  the method hasbeen implemented in the prototype available online  named ontorev  keywords  reasoning  revision  ontology  description logics  tableau methodchan 